description:
On February 6 the New York Times reported that Ronna McDaniel told Donald Trump she planned on resigning as Chairperson of the Republican National Committee (RNC) after the South Carolina Republican presidential primary, scheduled to take place on February 24.

This market will resolve to "Yes" if Ronna McDaniel steps down as RNC Chairperson between February 6 and the time main polling venues open on Super Tuesday, March 5, 2024 ET, 7:00 AM. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

An mere announcement made that Ronna McDaniel will step down as RNC Chairperson will NOT be sufficient to resolve this market to "Yes". This market will only resolve to "Yes" if Ronna McDaniel actually steps down as RNC Chairperson within this market's timeframe.

The primary resolution source for this market will be information from the RNC and Ronna McDaniel, however a consensus of credible reporting will also be used.
